Program: The Reith Lectures
Title: Critical Opposition - Part of the Policy
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00h2cpg
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 30 Nov 1983
Former Permanent Secretary to HM Treasury, Sir Douglas Wass explores the concept of authority in his series 'Government and the Governed'. In his fourth Reith Lecture entitled 'Critical Opposition - Part of the Policy', Sir Douglas Wass asks how effective Parliament is at exercising today the functions of supervision and control which the 17th-century reformers allotted to it. Show less